                   had lately served on board the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178307230105"></xptr> ship called the Sybill, and that certain prize money was due and payable to him; on the <rs id="t17830723-87-cd398" type="crimeDate">6th day of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17830723-87-off397 t17830723-87-cd398"></join> last, feloniously did forge and counterfeit, and procure to be forged and counterfeited, a certain letter of attorney from the said 
